1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:03,700
Developers spend hours inside the same work surface.

2
00:00:04,220 --> 00:00:11,240
Most themes are either too limited, or they cover the workspace,
break layout, and add background overhead.

3
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:19,300
Codex Dream Skin makes Codex personal without sacrificing
readability, stability, or control.

4
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,060
The workflow starts with a visual brief.

5
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:34,450
Codex and GPT-5.6 organize color, backgrounds,
original Image2 mecha-cat variants, semantic icons, and animation.

6
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:42,500
Every item has a role, version, release status,
and publication boundary.

7
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:45,920
This is not a static wallpaper.

8
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:52,860
The theme is split into independent background, character,
glass-surface, button, and interaction modules.

9
00:00:53,580 --> 00:01:04,300
Tests and payload budgets run first. Then a local CDP one-shot
applies modules without patching the official app.

10
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:08,420
After activation, native functions remain intact.

11
00:01:09,270 --> 00:01:13,980
The left navigation uses dimensional,
semantic cat-inspired icons.

12
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:18,200
The background preserves a readable work-safe area.
